On November 8, 2011, the White House sent several nominations to the Senate for confirmation. These nominations included Meredith M. Broadbent from Virginia to be a Member of the United States International Trade Commission, Anne Claire Richard from New York to be an Assistant Secretary of State for Population, Refugees, and Migration, and Tara D. Sonenshine from Maryland to be Under Secretary of State for Public Diplomacy. These nominations were made to fill vacant positions in the government.